type="local"
href="erct-000V.xml"
addr="erct-000V"
title="Equivalence of types">equivalences</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="true"
expanded="false"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>8558</fr:anchor><fr:addr>erct-000L</fr:addr><fr:route>erct-000L.xml</fr:route><fr:title>The univalence principle for <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000B.xml"
addr="erct-000B"
title="Precategory">precategories</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000L.agda">erct-000L.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For any <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000B.xml"
addr="erct-000B"
title="Precategory">precategory</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex>, the type <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({D : \mathsf {Precategory}}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({D : \mathsf {Precategory}}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({D : \mathsf {Precategory}}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \sum _{\mathopen {}\left ({D : \mathsf {Precategory}}\right )\mathclose {}}}{D\cong  C}]]></fr:tex> of <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000J.xml"
addr="erct-000J"
title="Isomorphism of precategories">isomorphisms of precategories</fr:link> onto <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001H.xml"
addr="erct-001H"
title="Contractible type">contractible</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3068</fr:anchor><fr:addr>#354</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-354.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>erct-000L</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>The type of isomorphisms onto <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is inhabited, considering the identity isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{C}\colon  C\cong  C]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, it suffices to show that the type of <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000J.xml"
addr="erct-000J"
title="Isomorphism of precategories">isomorphisms</fr:link> onto <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> depicted below is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">proposition</fr:link>:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[    \begin {aligned}     D &: \mathsf {Precategory}\\     F &: D\cong  C    \end {aligned}   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>We unfold the definitions of a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000B.xml"
addr="erct-000B"
title="Precategory">precategories</fr:link> and <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000J.xml"
addr="erct-000J"
title="Isomorphism of precategories">their isomorphisms</fr:link>, dropping <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001I.xml"
addr="erct-001I"
title="Proposition">propositional</fr:link> axioms:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     \begin {aligned}       D_0&: \mathsf {Type}\\       D_1&:D_0\to  D_0\to \mathsf {Set}\\       F_0&: D_0\to  C_0\\       F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y\in  D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y\in  D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y\in  D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y\in  D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}} D_1xy\to  C\mathopen {}\left ({F_0x,F_0y}\right )\mathclose {}\\       h_1 &: \mathsf {isBiinvertible}\,F_0\\       h_2 &: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}} \mathsf {isPropMap}\mathopen {}\left ({F_1xy}\right )\mathclose {}       \\       h_3 &: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}} \mathsf {isSurjection}\mathopen {}\left ({F_1xy}\right )\mathclose {}     \end {aligned}   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>A function that is both <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001T.xml"
addr="erct-001T"
title="N-truncated map">propositional</fr:link> and a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0029.xml"
addr="erct-0029"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link>, i.e. a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-003F.xml"
addr="erct-003F"
title="Bijection">bijection</fr:link>, is an <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000V.xml"
addr="erct-000V"
title="Equivalence of types">equivalence</fr:link> by <fr:ref
addr="erct-002Z"
taxon="Corollary" />. We can therefore repackage our telescope equivalently:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     \begin {aligned}       D_0&: \mathsf {Type}\\       D_1&:D_0\to  D_0\to \mathsf {Set}\\       F_0&: D_0\cong  C_0\\       F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y: D_0}\right )\mathclose {}}} D_1xy\cong  C\mathopen {}\left ({F_0x,F_0y}\right )\mathclose {}     \end {aligned}   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>By the univalence principle for types, we may contract <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left ({D_0,F_0}\right )\mathclose {}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  \lvert {C}\right  \rvert \mathclose {}, 1_{\mathopen {}\left  \lvert {C}\right  \rvert \mathclose {}}}\right )\mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     \begin {aligned}       D_1&:\mathopen {}\left  \lvert {C}\right  \rvert \mathclose {}\to  \mathopen {}\left  \lvert {C}\right  \rvert \mathclose {}\to \mathsf {Set}\\       F_1&: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y\in  C}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\textstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y\in  C}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y\in  C}\right )\mathclose {}}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{\mathopen {}\left ({x,y\in  C}\right )\mathclose {}}} D_1xy\cong  C\mathopen {}\left ({x,y}\right )\mathclose {}     \end {aligned}   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>Next we rewrite using the univalence principles for functions and families of types (<fr:ref
addr="erct-0015"
taxon="Axiom" />, <fr:ref
addr="erct-001D"
taxon="Axiom" />):</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     \begin {aligned}       D_1&:\mathopen {}\left  \lvert {C}\right  \rvert \mathclose {}\to  \mathopen {}\left  \lvert {C}\right  \rvert \mathclose {}\to \mathsf {Set}\\       F_1&: D_1 = \lambda {x,y}\mathpunct {.}{C\mathopen {}\left ({x,y}\right )\mathclose {}}     \end {aligned}   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>By the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0015.xml"
addr="erct-0015"
title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for functions</fr:link>, the data above is <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001H.xml"
addr="erct-001H"
title="Contractible type">contractible</fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
